{{nihongo|'''''Legend of Hero Tonma'''''|レジェンド・オブ・ヒーロー・トンマ}} is a [[side scrolling]] [[platform game]] released by [[Irem]] to [[Video arcade|arcades]] in 1989. The player controls a caped hero named Tommy in his quest to rescue a princess. Tommy can cast fireballs (which can be upgraded in power) to dispatch enemies, and jump on their heads to temporarily stun them.

The game was ported to the [[TurboGrafx-16]] in 1991 and localized to North America in 1993. The TurboGrafx-16 version was re-released on the [[Wii]] [[Virtual Console]] in Japan on September 4, 2007,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/wii/vc/software/04.html|title=Wii &#124; Virtual Console バーチャルコンソール|website=www.nintendo.co.jp |accessdate=July 10, 2022}}</ref> in North America on September 24,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.com/|title=Nintendo - Official Site - Video Game Consoles, Games|website=www.nintendo.com}}</ref> (delisted on March 30, 2012; returning in September 2013), and in PAL regions on September 28.<ref name=Europe>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nintendo.co.uk/Games/TurboGrafx/Legend-of-Hero-Tonma--277842.html|title=Legend of Hero Tonma™|website=Nintendo of Europe GmbH |accessdate=July 10, 2022}}</ref> The game was then released for the [[Wii U]] Virtual Console in Japan on March 18, 2015,<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.nintendo.co.jp/titles/20010000013529|title=レジェンド･オブ･ヒーロー･トンマ &#124; Wii U &#124; 任天堂|website=任天堂ホームページ}}</ref> and in North America and Europe on October 12, 2017.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nintendo.com/games/detail/legend-of-hero-tonma-wii-u/|title=Legend of Hero Tonma for Wii U - Nintendo Game Details|website=www.nintendo.com}}</ref><ref name=Europe/>

== Reception ==
In Japan, ''Game Machine'' listed ''Legend of Hero Tonma'' on their June 1, 1989 issue as being the tenth most-popular arcade game for the previous two weeks.<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Game Machine's Best Hit Games 25 - テーブル型TVゲーム機 (Table Videos)|magazine=[[:ja:ゲームマシン|Game Machine]]|issue=357 |publisher=[[:ja:アミューズメント通信社|Amusement Press, Inc.]]|date=1 June 1989|page=21|lang=ja}}</ref>

